President Trump delivered remarks at the swearing-in ceremony of Mark T. Esper as the new Secretary of Defense. Trump expressed his gratitude to the Department of Defense and praised the dedication and courage of the military. He highlighted Esper's qualifications and his commitment to national security. Trump also acknowledged the presence of other military leaders and thanked them for their service. He discussed the accomplishments of the military under his administration, such as increased defense spending and the defeat of ISIS. Trump emphasized the importance of border security and praised Mexico for deploying troops to assist in controlling the southern border. He also mentioned the establishment of the United States Space Force as a significant development. Trump concluded by reaffirming the commitment to protect the United States and its citizens.